  "text": "Image by The Escapist. | Published: Apr 23, 2025 10:33 am If you’ve always preferred Wile E. Coyote over Road Runner, Beaks is the perfect game for you. In order to shoot and collect as many different birds as possible, you need the best weapons to do so. Here’s all Beaks guns and where to find them. Table of contentsHow To Get All Guns In BeaksBeakwoods Area GunsQuill Lake Area GunsMount Beaks Area GunsDeadlands Area Guns How To Get All Guns In Beaks Screenshot by The Escapist. Right now, there’s 8 guns available for purchase in Beaks, located in 4 different areas. You get the first gun when you load into the game for the first time, while the rest are purchasable at four different markets. There’s no map in the game, but make sure to follow our guide and you’ll get to these markets in no time. Beakwoods Area Guns Screenshot by The Escapist. The Beakwoods area is the one in which you spawn every time you enter the game. Just behind the spawnpoint you’ll find Rowan, who’s in charge of what he calls the best beginner guns in all the land. Here you’ll find the stats of your beginner gun, as well as get the opportunity to purchase another gun: NameAppearancePriceRarityLevel RequirementDamage Per HitRangeSpeedFire RateAccuracyBeakwood RifleFreeCommon/55002500.5s84%Hunter’s Rifle$1500CommonLevel 585005000.5s86% Quill Lake Area Guns Screenshot by The Escapist. Drop down to the forest from the Beakwoods area and you’ll see a stone path on the right. Follow it until you reach a large hill. This hill, by the way, is a great vantage point for hunting the birds, but for now you need to go to its right and you’ll reach a lake area called Quill Lake.  Screenshot by The Escapist. The gun merchant, Colonel Amos, is located on a raft across the lighthouse and he can sell you two additional guns. These two are a bit more advanced than the ones you get at Beakwoods, and they serve as a great addition to your gameplay: NameAppearancePriceRarityLevel RequirementDamage Per HitRangeSpeedFire RateAccuracyLakeborne Shotgun$7500CommonLevel 1061003000.45s75%Lakeborne Rifle$12500UncommonLevel 15124004000.35s90% Mount Beaks Area Guns Screenshot by The Escapist. The best way to access this area is to drop down from the spawnpoint and go directly to your left. There’s another stone path that can help you out, but the moment you drop down in the woods you’ll see the Mount Beaks area sign. Climbing up the mountain is easier than it looks, and once you take the first right off the path you’ve arrived to the heart of Mount Beaks. Screenshot by The Escapist. Here you’ll find Flint, who can get you access to two new guns, stronger and more precise than the previous ones. Of course, this strength comes at a significantly steeper price both in money and the tediousness of climbing, but Mount Beaks is arguably the best position on the map to hunt birds because of its altitude. These two guns can help you out in that endeavour: NameAppearancePriceRarityLevel RequirementDamage Per HitRangeSpeedFire RateAccuracyMt. Beaks Long-Rifle$25000UncommonLevel 201610004000.3s85%Summit Rifle$17000RareLevel 25127506500.4s85% Deadlands Area Guns Screenshot by The Escapist. Remember that first path from the spawnpoint? This is where you need to be in order to unlock the last area on the map. Follow the stone path once you cross the lake and go all the way until its end. When you reach the Deadlands sign, you’ll see a vast area beneath you. You can go to your right where you’ll find another area sign and descend down the stairs – or, you know, just jump off the vantage point. There’s no dying in this game anyway. Once you’re down in the heart of Deadlands, you need to go to the left. Pass the weird scientist making a skeleton bird, pass the green fumes, keep left all the way until you reach the very end of the path, where you’ll find Commander Thorne, the gun merchant, inside the sole house. He can sell you the two strongest (and most expensive) guns in-game: NameAppearancePriceRarityLevel RequirementDamage Per HitRangeSpeedFire RateAccuracyDeadlands Long-Rifle$37500EpicLevel 30209006500.45s85%Viper Rifle$55000LegendaryLevel 35257505000.4s91% And that’s how to find all guns in Beaks. Choose whichever works best for you and collect the rarest birds with ease. Looking to chat to fellow players? Check out our Beaks Trello \u0026 Discord server links for all social links related to the game. The Escapist is supported by our audience. When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn a small affiliate commission. Learn more about our Affiliate Policy",
